<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="287"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Extend the generic ELFStreamer class so that it can emit mapping symbols at</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the appropriate points in the object files. These symbols are defined in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><Highlight kind="comment">/// AArch64 ELF ABI:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"><Highlight kind="comment">///    infocenter.arm.com/help/topic/com.arm.doc.ihi0056a/IHI0056A&#95;aaelf64.pdf</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><Highlight kind="comment">/// In brief: $x or $d should be emitted at the start of each contiguous region</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of A64 code or data in a section. In practice, this emission does not rely</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><Highlight kind="comment">/// on explicit assembler directives but on inherent properties of the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><Highlight kind="comment">/// directives doing the emission (e.g. &quot;.byte&quot; is data, &quot;add x0, x0, x0&quot; an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><Highlight kind="comment">/// instruction).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><Highlight kind="comment">/// As a result this system is orthogonal to the DataRegion infrastructure used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><Highlight kind="comment">/// by MachO. Beware!</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-aarch64elfstreamer-cpp-/aarch64elfstreamer"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-aarch64elfstreamer-cpp-/aarch64elfstreamer/#ab3c1d7ab672f0bd15bc00752eb7f8c4d">AArch64ELFStreamer</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcelfstreamer/#aec09c5b9322b90f034d51bd3c0903563">MCELFStreamer</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Save the mapping symbol state for potential reuse when revisiting the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// section. When ImplicitMapSyms is true, the initial state is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// EMS&#95;A64 for text sections and EMS&#95;Data for the others.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="normal">    LastMappingSymbols&#91;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcstreamer/#ad946e0775ff08232ff6dc1bd9a8ed9bb">getCurrentSection</a>().first&#93; = LastEMS;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> It = LastMappingSymbols.find(Section);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (It != LastMappingSymbols.end())</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (ImplicitMapSyms)</Highlight></CodeLine>
